
  # Data Storage System

This diagram shows how patient data is stored and accessed in the system. The main class is DataStorage, which keeps all patient data in one place.

DataStorage has a composition relationship with Patient, and Patient has composition with PatientRecord. I used composition here because patients belong to the storage, and records belong to the patient. If a patient is removed, their records should also be removed, so this shows strong ownership.

The DataReader interface has a dependency to DataStorage. This is because it reads data and sends it to storage, but it does not keep it. It only uses DataStorage as a parameter, so a dependency is the correct relationship.

DataRetriever is connected to DataStorage and AccessController with associations. It uses both of them to retrieve data. It gets the records from storage and checks permissions through AccessController. I kept this separate from DataStorage so that querying logic and storage logic are not mixed.

AccessController is used to control who can access patient data. It checks roles before allowing access, which is important for security.

RetentionPolicy is connected to DataStorage because storage uses it to decide when old data should be deleted. This shows that deletion logic is separated from storage.
